scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Oral histories, memoirs, research files, photographs, newsclippings, maps, publications, adobe house preservation work, etc. Included is a 1870 census of Chinese workers, adobe samples from the house, information about the adobe structure, the historic structure report, the original house plan, the Juana Briones house tour docent handbook, "The Story of Donna Juana Briones de Miranda, " by Catherine Crary Elwood, 1962.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Juana Briones (1802-1899) was a businesswoman and landowner in the San Francisco Bay Area.

odd.head: General
odd.p: These materials were collected by students in the Stanford History 201 course taught by Carol McKibben during the fall of 2009. The materials were given to Stanford University Libraries by various donors. At the time of this class, the historic adobe house was still standing but slated for demolition.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research; material must be requested at least 36 hours in advance of intended use.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [identification of item], Juana Briones collection (M1706). Dept. of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Gift of various donors, transferred to Special Collections, 2009 and 2012. Accessions 2009-241 and 2012-124.
